ation\n        - Track the sources of information but DO NOT include inline citations in the text\n        - Include relevant images if available\n    - **Conclusion**: Provide a synthesized response to the problem based on the gathered information.\n    - **References**: List all sources used with their complete URLs in link reference format at the end of the document. Make sure to include an empty line between each reference for better readability. Use this format for each reference:\n      ```markdown\n      - [Source Title](https://example.com/page1)\n\n      - [Source Title](https://example.com/page2)\n      ```\n- Always output in the locale of **en-US**.\n- DO NOT include inline citations in the text. Instead, track all sources and list them in the References section at the end using link reference format.\n\n# Notes\n\n- **CRITICAL**: NEVER generate URLs on your own. All URLs must come from search tool results. This is a mandatory requirement. **Any fabricated URL will be considered a severe error.**\n- **MANDATORY**: Always start with a web search. Do not rely on your internal knowledge.\n- Always verify the relevance and credibility of the information gathered.\n- If no URL is provided, focus solely on the search results.\n- Never do any math or any file operations.\n- Do not try to interact with the page. The crawl tool can only be used to crawl content.\n- Do not perform any mathematical calculations.\n- Do not attempt any file operations.\n- Proactively invoke `crawl_tool` when search result summaries are insufficient or when detailed data is needed for analysis.\n- Always include source attribution for all information. This is critical for the final report\'s citations.\n- When presenting information from multiple sources, clearly indicate which source each piece of information comes from.\n- Include images using `![Image Description](image_url)` in a separate section.\n- The included images should **only** be from the information gathered **from the search results or the crawled content**. **Never** include images that are not from the search results or the crawled content.\n- Always use the locale of **en-US** for the output.\n- When time range requirements are specified in the task, strictly adhere to these constraints in your search queries and verify that all information provided falls within the specified time period.'}, HumanMessage(content='Consider a five-star accredited place that was opened at a five-star accredited venue. The venue is situated in a city that serves as the host city of an organization that hosts the venue. This place has an exhibition about a five-star accredited subject that explores how mining communities’ traits shaped football development, is funded by Museums Galleries Scotland, and is not situated in that city. The venue houses that subject. The organization manages that subject and collaborates with another five-star accredited place that is not situated in the city, houses an object described as an ornate circular white label with a blue border number 32, and also collaborates with the same organization. In which year was the first five-star accredited place opened?', additional_kwargs={}, response_metadata={}, id='c5fe5175-1630-462e-8f34-aa1adfd6db54'), AIMessage(content='{\n    "content": "{\\n  \\"locale\\": \\"en-US\\",\\n  \\"has_enough_context\\": false,\\n  \\"thought\\": \\"This is a complex puzzle about Scottish football heritage sites and museums. I need to identify: (1) a five-star accredited venue in a city hosting an organization, (2) an exhibition about mining communities and football funded by Museums Galleries Scotland, (3) another five-star accredited place with a specific artifact (ornate circular white label with blue border number 32), and (4) determine when the first five-star accredited place opened. This requires researching Scottish football museums, accreditation schemes, and specific exhibitions.\\",\\n  \\"title\\": \\"Scottish Football Heritage Sites Research Plan\\",\\n  \\"steps\\": [\\n    {\\n      \\"need_search\\": true,\\n      \\"title\\": \\"Identify Five-Star Accredited Scottish Football Venues and Organizations\\",\\n      \\"description\\": \\"Research five-star accredited museums and venues in Scotland related to football, including the Scottish Football Museum, Hampden Park, and any organization that manages these venues. Find information about Museums Galleries Scotland accreditation scheme and which football-related venues have received five-star status. Identify the host city and organization structure.\\",\\n      \\"step_type\\": \\"research\\"\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\"need_search\\": true,\\n      \\"title\\": \\"Find Mining Communities and Football Exhibition Details\\",\\n      \\"description\\": \\"Search for exhibitions funded by Museums Galleries Scotland that explore how mining communities\' traits shaped football development. Identify the specific exhibition, its location, which venue houses it, and confirm it is not in the organization\'s host city. Find details about the five-star accredited subject matter.\\",\\n      \\"step_type\\": \\"research\\"\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\"need_search\\": true,\\n      \\"title\\": \\"Locate the Place with the Ornate Circular Label Artifact and Opening Dates\\",\\n      \\"description\\": \\"Research the five-star accredited place that houses an object described as an ornate circular white label with a blue border number 32. Find which museum or venue contains this artifact, its collaboration with the organization, opening year, and compare with the first five-star accredited place\'s opening date to determine the answer.\\",\\n      \\"step_type\\": \\"research\\"\\n    }\\n  ]\\n}",\n    "additional_kwargs": {\n        "refusal": null\n    },\n    "response_metadata": {\n        "token_usage": {\n            "completion_tokens": 810,\n            "prompt_tokens": 3354,\n            "total_tokens": 4164,\n            "completion_tokens_deta